public final class CharArray extends PrimitiveArray implements CharList
A dynamic array of primitive char values. Supports the indexing operations in CharList. Expands the size of the array if you call set(int, char) or add(char) and the array is not big enough.

Constructors take the same name, maximum size and estimated capacity that all PrimitiveCollections take. In addition a CharArray can construct from part or all of a primitive char[].

A sub-array can be retrieved by specifying the starting index and the length with subArray(int, int). The sub-array is read only and will share data with the underlying parent array for efficiency.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
